article.headline: Robert Morris 55, St. Peter's 30
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Karon Abraham scored 14 points and Robert Morris defeated St. Peter's 55-30 Saturday, scoring more points in the second half than St. Peter's scored in the game. In the season opener for both teams, the Peacocks seldom found the basket, making only 6 of 36 attempts from the field and only half (16 of 32) from the free-throw line. The Colonials took advantage of 21 St. Peter's turnovers, and outscored the Peacocks 26-2 on turnover opportunities. They scored 32 points in the second half to build on a 23-13 halftime lead. Russell Johnson added 12 points while Yann Charles contributed 10 points for Robert Morris. Nick Leon led St. Peter's with 13 points, making 8 of 9 from the line. The rest of his teammates were 8 of 23 on free throws and nobody else scored in double-figures for the Peacocks. Ryan Bacon had 10 rebounds and three blocked shots for St. Peter's.
